search::buildWhereClause()

Description
    private string search::buildWhereClause(array $keywords)
    Builds a valid where clause to complement a MySQL query string.  This where clause is contained in a string generated according to the contents of   
    $keywords.

Parameters
    keywords
    An array containing one or more instances of "and", "not", or "*".

Return Values
    A string variable containing a MySQL where clause.

Examples
    <?php
	...
	if (empty($keywords)) {
	    $this->relevanceSearch = FALSE;
	}

	$this->query['where'] = $this->buildWhereClause($keywords);
		
	foreach ($this->query['where'] as $where) {
	    if (!in_array(strtolower($where),$this->boolOperands)) {
		$this->query['selectRelevance'][] = "(CASE WHEN ".$where." THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)";
	    }
	}
	...
    ?>
   
See Also
    search::createQuery()
    search::buildQuery()
